EU Commission proposes new court in dispute over TTIP
In order to defuse the dispute over the planned transatlantic free trade agreement TTIP, the EU Commission has proposed a major reform of the current arbitration system.
The controversial private arbitration bodies for disputes between corporations and states are to be replaced by a more transparent system, which corresponds to significantly more traditional courts in its functioning.
"We want to set up a system that citizens trust," said the European Commissioner Cecilia Malmström at the presentation.
Sweden intends to introduce the proposal as a European negotiating position in the free trade talks with the US.
