Pound rises from accelerated wage growth in UK
The pound jumped up after data showing a rise in UK wage growth. In parallel, the FTSE 100 was increased by the SABMiller bid target.
Between May and July, earnings excluding bonuses in the UK grew by 2.9% compared with the same period last year.
This percentage has been the fastest since 2009 and provided estimates of the timing of an increase in interest rates.
